WEBVTT

00:06.441 --> 00:09.139
- Previously, on "Happy!"...
- "Easter Under Siege."

00:09.183 --> 00:10.749
We're a hit, baby!

00:10.793 --> 00:12.360
- I run the third-largest
network in the nation.

00:12.403 --> 00:14.144
I have everything
a man could wish for.

00:14.188 --> 00:15.711
- What about the things
a man shouldn't wish for?

00:15.754 --> 00:17.408
- You're firing me.

00:17.452 --> 00:18.540
- You don't give me any choice!

00:18.583 --> 00:20.759
- There is something inside me.

00:20.803 --> 00:22.413
[heavy electronic music]

00:22.457 --> 00:24.850
I'm done being
everyone's bitch, Dr. Reddy.

00:24.894 --> 00:26.417
[dramatic music]

00:26.461 --> 00:29.855
- You know you are
a dead man, Blue rat.

00:29.899 --> 00:33.555
- You, me,
under the bleachers.

00:33.598 --> 00:36.210
- No!
Help me!

00:36.253 --> 00:38.125
- You almost got hurt
back there.

00:38.168 --> 00:40.214
- Looking for these?

00:40.257 --> 00:41.737
You knew I needed money
for Hailey's school.

00:41.780 --> 00:43.130
You used me, Mer.

00:43.173 --> 00:44.609
- Yeah, I did.
- Yeah.

00:44.653 --> 00:46.307
This very simple
"B and E" of yours,

00:46.350 --> 00:48.526
it turned out not to be
quite so simple.

00:48.570 --> 00:49.832
Sonny Shine.

00:49.875 --> 00:51.747
A few guards showed up.
- And?

00:51.790 --> 00:53.792
- And I'm standing here
with the tapes.

00:53.836 --> 00:55.272
- Proof is on these tapes.

00:55.316 --> 00:57.361
The people on these tapes
protect him.

00:57.405 --> 00:59.537
He goes down, they go down.

00:59.581 --> 01:02.453
- Holy guacamole,
it's Dayglo Doug!

01:02.497 --> 01:03.628
- [singing indistinctly]

01:03.672 --> 01:05.848
- Who the fuck's Dayglo Doug?

01:05.891 --> 01:09.634
♪

01:10.635 --> 01:12.202
[peppy music]

01:12.246 --> 01:13.769
- Here we go!

01:13.812 --> 01:15.423
Abracadabra!

01:15.466 --> 01:17.729
♪

01:17.773 --> 01:19.122
Bunny!

01:19.166 --> 01:20.819
Ow, oh!
I'm Julius Caesar!

01:20.863 --> 01:23.866
You can't do this to me!
[comical groaning]

01:23.909 --> 01:26.521
- Say something sweet
and eat something sour.

01:26.564 --> 01:27.957
Magic and laughs

01:28.000 --> 01:30.786
on the
"Dayglo Doug Power Hour"!

01:30.829 --> 01:33.180
- Yeah!

01:33.223 --> 01:34.616
Hey, there!

01:34.659 --> 01:37.271
Uh, no, no, no, no.
No applause.

01:37.314 --> 01:38.533
No applause.

01:38.576 --> 01:41.405
I am not worthy.
Thank you.

01:42.667 --> 01:45.670
[ominous rumbling]

01:46.671 --> 01:49.674
[high-pitched tone]

01:50.980 --> 01:52.764
- We love you!
- Yeah!

01:52.808 --> 01:55.202
- We love you, Doug!

01:55.245 --> 01:57.291
- And it's that love...

01:57.334 --> 02:00.381
that has made
"The Dayglo Doug Power Hour"

02:00.424 --> 02:03.384
the top-rated
cable-access kid's show

02:03.427 --> 02:05.473
in the greater Toledo area.

02:05.516 --> 02:07.344
[cheers and applause]

02:07.388 --> 02:10.173
And only a handful of shows
can make that claim.

02:15.004 --> 02:16.310
But...

02:17.920 --> 02:21.576
The time has come
for old Doug...

02:21.619 --> 02:23.534
to hang up his hat.

02:25.362 --> 02:27.190
This will be
the last day I host

02:27.234 --> 02:30.498
the "Dayglo Doug Power Hour."

02:30.541 --> 02:33.544
children: Aww, no!
[exclaiming]

02:36.460 --> 02:39.246
- Before I get too emotional...

02:41.465 --> 02:42.858
I wanna introduce you

02:42.901 --> 02:45.904
to the new host
of the power hour,

02:45.948 --> 02:49.517
and your new best friend...

02:49.560 --> 02:51.867
Sonny Shine!

02:51.910 --> 02:54.435
- [hollering]

02:54.478 --> 02:57.438
[children cheering]

02:57.481 --> 03:00.702
♪

03:00.745 --> 03:03.879
[goofy babbling]

03:06.751 --> 03:09.493
Dayglo Doug, everybody!

03:09.537 --> 03:12.757
[laughing]
His best trick?

03:12.801 --> 03:15.499
Vanishing from his own show.

03:15.543 --> 03:18.285
[cruel laugh]
But seriously, Doug.

03:18.328 --> 03:21.331
Now you'll have plenty of time
to devote to your...

03:21.375 --> 03:23.028
passions.

03:23.072 --> 03:25.292
You may not know it,
but our buddy Doug

03:25.335 --> 03:26.989
is quite the aficionado
on a little something

03:27.032 --> 03:28.860
you might have studied
in school:

03:28.904 --> 03:31.515
World War II.

03:31.559 --> 03:33.735
[dark music]

03:33.778 --> 03:35.606
Look it up.

03:35.650 --> 03:37.347
But I've been thinking,
Double-D.

03:37.391 --> 03:40.959
Will you even have time
to join us as a guest star?

03:41.003 --> 03:42.918
- Sure, that--that'd be super.

03:42.961 --> 03:46.574
- But then I think about
Episode 186.

03:46.617 --> 03:48.924
- "Episode 186"?

03:48.967 --> 03:50.447
The Band-Aid episode?

03:50.491 --> 03:51.883
- [trilling]
Correcto.

03:51.927 --> 03:53.102
Where you taught us all how

03:53.145 --> 03:55.104
tearing off
the Band-Aid quickly

03:55.147 --> 03:58.455
was really the only healthy way
to move forward.

03:58.499 --> 04:00.849
Isn't that right, kids?

04:00.892 --> 04:02.590
[children cheering]

04:02.633 --> 04:05.593
[echoing laughter]

04:05.636 --> 04:06.942
♪

04:06.985 --> 04:09.858
- And now, let's cue the music.

04:09.901 --> 04:12.643
Because we'd all like
to remember you...

04:12.687 --> 04:15.603
just the way you are.

04:15.646 --> 04:18.562
[John Kander's
"Tomorrow Belongs To Me"]

04:18.606 --> 04:21.913
- ♪ Oh, fatherland,
fatherland ♪

04:21.957 --> 04:24.351
♪ Show us a sign

04:24.394 --> 04:29.094
♪ Your children
are waiting to see ♪

04:29.138 --> 04:31.923
[frantic]
♪ The morning will come

04:31.967 --> 04:33.882
♪ When the world

04:33.925 --> 04:37.407
[screaming]
♪ Is mine

04:37.451 --> 04:40.802
♪ Tomorrow belongs

04:40.845 --> 04:43.500
♪ To me

04:43.544 --> 04:45.459
Doug?

04:45.502 --> 04:47.852
Doug, one question
for the aficionado

04:47.896 --> 04:50.333
before you go:

04:50.377 --> 04:53.945
About how tall would you say
Winston Churchill was?

04:53.989 --> 04:55.556
- Churchill?

04:55.599 --> 04:57.949
About that tall.

04:57.993 --> 04:59.473
[children shouting]

04:59.516 --> 05:01.779
- Imagine it:
Dayglo Doug was there

05:01.823 --> 05:03.520
when Sonny started.

05:03.564 --> 05:06.001
What's the world, uh,
when you're part of history?

05:06.044 --> 05:08.525
- "Fossil."
- Yeah, Sax, I get it.

05:08.569 --> 05:10.092
He's old.
What's your point?

05:10.135 --> 05:12.616
- I dunno, let's see:
He's senile, wears leotards.

05:12.660 --> 05:14.575
No, sounds like
a slam-dunk witness

05:14.618 --> 05:16.054
to build the foundation
of your case on.

05:16.098 --> 05:18.187
Top flight police work, Mer,
digging up this gem.

05:18.230 --> 05:20.494
- It's not my case.
It's ours.

05:20.537 --> 05:22.800
Remember?

05:22.844 --> 05:24.672
We're here.

05:24.715 --> 05:27.370
[sinister musical flair]

05:29.111 --> 05:31.461
[conspiratorial music]

05:31.505 --> 05:33.985
- Cut my beard off after 9/11.

05:34.029 --> 05:35.639
- And you're here to see?

05:35.683 --> 05:37.989
- Doug Thorn.

05:38.033 --> 05:40.209
♪

05:40.252 --> 05:42.080
- Mr. Thorn
doesn't take visitors.

05:42.124 --> 05:44.387
♪

05:44.431 --> 05:46.694
- He'll make an exception.

05:46.737 --> 05:49.044
♪

05:49.087 --> 05:51.525
- Did you get that
out of a Cracker Jack box?

05:51.568 --> 05:53.091
- It was my dad's.

05:53.135 --> 05:56.617
- You really stepped in number
two with that one, Nick.

05:56.660 --> 05:59.054
- I'll step on you.

05:59.097 --> 06:01.535
♪

06:01.578 --> 06:03.232
- What's the matter?

06:03.275 --> 06:05.843
- Old people.

06:05.887 --> 06:07.410
- What?

06:07.454 --> 06:08.846
- They don't like me,
I don't like them.

06:08.890 --> 06:10.065
And that whole building
is filled with them.

06:10.108 --> 06:12.110
You smell that?

06:12.154 --> 06:13.895
That's them.

06:15.984 --> 06:17.768
Whoa, whoa.
Hey, psst.

06:17.812 --> 06:19.248
Hey, pal, pal.

06:19.291 --> 06:21.076
Hey, hey, you mind?
- For residents only.

06:21.119 --> 06:22.991
- Yeah, I got
a blood sugar thing.

06:23.034 --> 06:24.471
- If you're hungry,

06:24.514 --> 06:26.560
there's a vending machine
in the restroom.

06:26.603 --> 06:29.171
- "The restroom"?
Fuck this place.

06:29.214 --> 06:30.607
[goofy yelp]
Geez!

06:30.651 --> 06:32.130
- [electronic voice]
Are you my son?

06:33.828 --> 06:36.570
- Dr. Kevorkian's that way.

06:39.224 --> 06:40.748
[PA beeping]

06:40.791 --> 06:41.749
- Thank you.

06:41.792 --> 06:43.533
Uh, for my next trick,

06:43.577 --> 06:45.927
I would like you to look...

06:45.970 --> 06:47.929
at this hat.

06:47.972 --> 06:49.583
What do you see inside?

06:49.626 --> 06:51.846
Nothing, right?

06:53.151 --> 06:55.850
- Is that really Dayglo Doug?

06:55.893 --> 06:58.243
He looks different.

06:58.287 --> 07:01.116
- Get to the Polish jokes!

07:01.159 --> 07:02.596
- There's your star witness.

07:02.639 --> 07:04.075
- I will punch you
in the throat.

07:04.119 --> 07:06.469
- [clears throat]
So, man comes home from work

07:06.513 --> 07:08.210
with a duck under his arm.

07:08.253 --> 07:09.864
His wife answers the door.

07:09.907 --> 07:11.605
"This is the pig
I've been fucking,"

07:11.648 --> 07:13.084
the man says.

07:13.128 --> 07:15.086
The wife says,
"That's a duck, not a pig."

07:15.130 --> 07:17.959
The man says,
"I'm not talking to you."

07:18.002 --> 07:19.482
- [guffaws]

07:19.526 --> 07:23.573
- [goofy laughter]

07:23.617 --> 07:24.705
I don't get it.

07:24.748 --> 07:26.881
- I was going to close this set

07:26.924 --> 07:29.231
by cutting a woman in half.

07:29.274 --> 07:31.320
Unfortunately...

07:31.363 --> 07:34.192
my assistant passed away
this morning,

07:34.236 --> 07:38.501
so I would like
to dedicate today's show...

07:38.545 --> 07:39.763
to Gladys.

07:40.590 --> 07:42.157
She died as she lived.

07:42.200 --> 07:44.855
- Showing off her box
for a nickel?

07:44.899 --> 07:47.162
[laughter]

07:47.205 --> 07:50.165
- [laughing]

07:50.208 --> 07:53.081
[dark music]

07:53.124 --> 07:54.952
- Mr. Thorn?

07:54.996 --> 07:56.954
May we have a few words?

07:56.998 --> 07:59.087
- Ugh...

07:59.130 --> 08:02.003
[stuffy music]

08:02.046 --> 08:04.658
- Big as a baby's arm
with an apple in its fist.

08:04.701 --> 08:07.182
- I think the word
you're looking for is "jumbo."

08:07.225 --> 08:09.140
- I'm immune to flattery.

08:09.184 --> 08:10.881
And disease.

08:10.925 --> 08:13.318
Now spill it, cops.
Who violated my inner sanctum?

08:13.362 --> 08:15.016
- There's a loaded question.

08:15.059 --> 08:16.670
- Can we talk...

08:16.713 --> 08:18.628
openly?

08:18.672 --> 08:20.282
- Dario doesn't understand
a lick of English.

08:20.325 --> 08:22.197
- Hold still.

08:22.240 --> 08:25.853
♪

08:25.896 --> 08:27.898
- TBH...

08:27.942 --> 08:30.074
we, uh, don't have a lot
to go on.

08:30.118 --> 08:32.207
- And by that we mean
"nada surf."

08:32.250 --> 08:34.818
- And seeing as how
you wiped the whole place clean

08:34.862 --> 08:36.385
before we got here...

08:36.428 --> 08:38.648
- Well, this crime scene's got
more blood traces

08:38.692 --> 08:41.303
than Chicago
on St. Valentine's Day.

08:41.346 --> 08:42.957
- But no bodies.

08:43.000 --> 08:45.176
- The only witness
was your wife.

08:45.220 --> 08:46.700
She...

08:46.743 --> 08:48.005
fingered the pool boy.

08:48.049 --> 08:49.790
- Don't remind me.

08:49.833 --> 08:52.706
- Who she says was here
with a little blue unicorn.

08:52.749 --> 08:54.055
♪

08:54.098 --> 08:55.143
With wings.

08:55.186 --> 08:56.666
- Bebe's last coherent thought

08:56.710 --> 08:59.930
was during
the Carter administration.

08:59.974 --> 09:01.671
You're missing the point.

09:01.715 --> 09:03.934
This is not
an official investigation.

09:03.978 --> 09:05.414
There will be
no official reports

09:05.457 --> 09:07.982
of any stiffs on my grounds.

09:08.025 --> 09:09.723
There will be no
official statements taken

09:09.766 --> 09:12.900
from my smoking hot wife
or anyone else.

09:12.943 --> 09:14.902
But I do expect a very firm,

09:14.945 --> 09:17.121
hard, unofficial look

09:17.165 --> 09:20.255
into who the hell
effed up my effigy!

09:20.298 --> 09:23.084
That's why you two
are unofficially here!

09:23.127 --> 09:24.433
Is that clear?

09:24.476 --> 09:25.956
- As Mother Teresa's
urine test.

09:26.000 --> 09:27.392
- Ain't what I heard.

09:27.436 --> 09:29.307
- Magnifico!

09:29.351 --> 09:32.093
- No, no!
[speaking Italian]

09:32.136 --> 09:34.791
I want it
to look like the roots

09:34.835 --> 09:37.315
of a banyan tree.

09:37.359 --> 09:42.843
♪

09:42.886 --> 09:45.802
- Sonny Shine?

09:45.846 --> 09:47.064
No sir-ee.

09:47.108 --> 09:48.762
Sorry, can't help you.

09:48.805 --> 09:51.242
I am not gonna say
one word about him.

09:51.286 --> 09:53.070
"El zippo."

09:53.114 --> 09:55.812
- We're investigating
some serious crimes, Mr. Thorn.

09:55.856 --> 09:59.294
A child kidnapping ring,
murder, extortion.

09:59.337 --> 10:01.339
- Yeah, that sounds like Sonny.

10:03.037 --> 10:05.126
You two don't look like cops.

10:05.169 --> 10:06.344
- We're undercover.

10:06.388 --> 10:08.738
- Deep cover.

10:08.782 --> 10:10.827
I said it's deep, that's all.

10:12.524 --> 10:14.352
- I can tell you want
to talk to me, Doug.

10:14.396 --> 10:15.745
What are you afraid of?

10:15.789 --> 10:17.181
- [scoffs]
Me?

10:17.225 --> 10:18.313
Everything.

10:18.356 --> 10:20.663
Heights, spider plants,

10:20.707 --> 10:22.099
three-legged jeans.

10:22.143 --> 10:23.927
- [giggles]
He's still got it.

10:23.971 --> 10:25.320
- Oh, he's still got it,
all right.

10:25.363 --> 10:26.974
I just hope you can't catch it.

10:27.017 --> 10:30.151
- Listen, I can offer you
police protection.

10:30.194 --> 10:31.761
A new identity.
- [scoffs]

10:31.805 --> 10:33.197
"New identity."
That's a laugher.

10:33.241 --> 10:36.505
All I ever wanted
was my old one back.

10:36.548 --> 10:39.116
The rat bastard
stole everything from me.

10:39.160 --> 10:42.076
[devious music]

10:42.119 --> 10:43.512
- Yeah.

10:43.555 --> 10:45.819
Yeah, yeah.

10:45.862 --> 10:47.429
[sucks teeth]

10:47.472 --> 10:49.866
Sure isn't like
the old days, is it?

10:49.910 --> 10:52.303
Not like when
the "Dayglo Doug Power Hour"

10:52.347 --> 10:55.176
was the number one
kid's local access show

10:55.219 --> 10:58.092
in the greater Toledo area.

10:58.135 --> 11:00.181
You were big, Doug.

11:00.224 --> 11:01.835
- I was.

11:01.878 --> 11:03.706
I was big, wasn't I?

11:03.750 --> 11:06.361
- Johnny "Wadd" Holmes big.

11:06.404 --> 11:08.232
♪

11:08.276 --> 11:10.931
- Milton Berle big.

11:10.974 --> 11:13.020
[distant children cheering]

11:13.063 --> 11:17.502
- ♪ Give me a home

11:17.546 --> 11:20.462
♪ Where the buffalo roam

11:20.505 --> 11:25.815
♪ And the deer
and the antelope ♪

11:25.859 --> 11:28.339
♪ And seldom is heard

11:28.383 --> 11:31.255
- Shh.

11:31.299 --> 11:33.040
- ♪ A discouraging word

11:33.083 --> 11:36.304
- You know, I was there
to hear the great Caruso

11:36.347 --> 11:39.873
make his professional debut.

11:39.916 --> 11:43.877
Now I've got to listen
to this shit.

11:43.920 --> 11:46.967
- Do you not know the meaning
of "solitary confinement"?

11:47.010 --> 11:49.099
[sinister music]

11:49.143 --> 11:50.971
It's meant to be
just me in here!

11:51.014 --> 11:52.059
- Mm.

11:52.102 --> 11:53.538
Perhaps you're confused--

11:53.582 --> 11:56.106
which seems to happen
so very easily.

11:56.150 --> 11:57.891
So to elucidate,

11:57.934 --> 12:02.156
you are trapped
in this prison.

12:02.199 --> 12:05.333
I am trapped in you.

12:05.376 --> 12:06.464
♪

12:06.508 --> 12:08.249
- "Trapped"?

12:08.292 --> 12:10.381
Well, then, just...

12:10.425 --> 12:13.167
get out.

12:13.210 --> 12:15.865
I bequeath you freedom.

12:15.909 --> 12:18.433
- Mm, if only.

12:18.476 --> 12:20.914
But even the demigods
are constrained

12:20.957 --> 12:24.265
by certain earthly limitations.

12:24.308 --> 12:25.962
Bloodlines and all that.

12:26.006 --> 12:27.398
You know.

12:27.442 --> 12:30.924
I did try and hop into
your charming sister.

12:30.967 --> 12:34.275
Much more fun body
to play around in.

12:34.318 --> 12:37.800
Even came with its own
television show.

12:37.844 --> 12:39.280
But we both know how

12:39.323 --> 12:41.499
that little harlequin art
came to an end.

12:41.543 --> 12:43.501
- [sobbing]

12:43.545 --> 12:46.809
This is madness!

12:46.853 --> 12:49.377
I gotta get out of here!

12:49.420 --> 12:52.336
- It's not such a bad place
for us, this.

12:52.380 --> 12:55.035
At least until
I get my strength back.

12:55.078 --> 12:58.081
Pottery Shop.
Fun.

12:58.125 --> 13:01.389
And all these impressionable,

13:01.432 --> 13:03.913
homicidal minds to sway.

13:03.957 --> 13:06.307
♪

13:06.350 --> 13:08.831
And as I get my strength back,

13:08.875 --> 13:10.572
you'll have more
and more blackouts

13:10.615 --> 13:14.619
until life is one long,
continuous blackout.

13:14.663 --> 13:17.666
Now, won't that be nice?

13:17.709 --> 13:21.452
No more waking up
like a Kennedy, wondering...

13:21.496 --> 13:24.542
"Who did I sodomize?

13:24.586 --> 13:26.414
Whom did I kill?"

13:26.457 --> 13:28.024
- And what'll happen then?

13:28.068 --> 13:31.114
- By then, I'll have
built an army.

13:31.158 --> 13:33.160
- No.
[stammering]

13:33.203 --> 13:35.336
I meant what will happen to me.

13:35.379 --> 13:36.554
- Oh.

13:39.949 --> 13:42.865
[door buzzes]

13:44.040 --> 13:46.347
[bike bell ringing]

13:46.390 --> 13:48.610
- Uh, it's--
it's a great surprise.

13:48.653 --> 13:51.004
Don't get me wrong,
I like this new rebel Amanda.

13:51.047 --> 13:53.658
This "let's get crazy
and ditch work,

13:53.702 --> 13:55.182
good girl gone bad" Amanda.

13:55.225 --> 13:59.012
- You're joking,
but honestly...

13:59.055 --> 14:00.970
I know me.

14:01.014 --> 14:03.538
And these days, I haven't
felt like her at all.

14:03.581 --> 14:05.061
- Mm.

14:05.105 --> 14:06.933
- It's strange even
talking about it.

14:06.976 --> 14:08.369
- Not at all.

14:08.412 --> 14:11.546
Talking it out is the best way
to deal with stress.

14:11.589 --> 14:14.288
That and a little hot yoga.

14:14.331 --> 14:17.073
- I don't think hot yoga's
gonna fix it.

14:19.162 --> 14:21.251
Ugh.
I got fired, Simon.

14:21.295 --> 14:23.514
- Seriously?

14:23.558 --> 14:25.995
That's great.

14:26.039 --> 14:27.214
- Um--

14:27.257 --> 14:28.650
- I was right out of college
in Seattle

14:28.693 --> 14:30.260
when the first
big dot-com boom hit.

14:30.304 --> 14:31.958
I found myself one
of the first employees

14:32.001 --> 14:33.960
in a little
books-in-the-mail startup.

14:34.003 --> 14:35.657
- Amazon?
Wow.

14:35.700 --> 14:38.921
No, it was
EncyclopediasInTheMail.com.

14:38.965 --> 14:40.401
Free returns killed us.

14:40.444 --> 14:43.665
So six months later
I'm broke, I'm unemployed.

14:43.708 --> 14:45.319
Living in my mother's basement.

14:45.362 --> 14:47.408
I was feeling sorry for myself.

14:47.451 --> 14:49.149
But it forced me to do a lot

14:49.192 --> 14:51.064
of soul-searching,
Amanda, okay?

14:51.107 --> 14:53.327
To figure out
what I really want in life.

14:53.370 --> 14:54.937
What's really important.

14:54.981 --> 14:57.070
I realized, for me,
it's giving back.

14:57.113 --> 14:59.159
Making a difference.

14:59.202 --> 15:00.334
Boom.

15:00.377 --> 15:02.771
"Ties Without Borders"
was born.

15:02.814 --> 15:04.468
Mm?

15:04.512 --> 15:05.992
You feel me?

15:09.169 --> 15:11.954
- Every setback
is an opportunity?

15:11.998 --> 15:13.782
- To learn something
about yourself.

15:13.825 --> 15:17.786
To bring something new
into this world.

15:17.829 --> 15:20.658
Joseph Campbell said it best:

15:20.702 --> 15:22.182
"Follow your bliss."

15:22.225 --> 15:24.140
He should know.

15:24.184 --> 15:26.621
He invented
frickin' "Star Wars."

15:28.014 --> 15:29.319
- I like that.

15:31.017 --> 15:33.671
"Follow your bliss."

15:33.715 --> 15:36.761
[classical music]

15:36.805 --> 15:39.808
- [groaning]
Yes, yes, yes!

15:39.851 --> 15:41.984
Simon!
Yes!

15:42.028 --> 15:44.160
[both moaning, grunting]

15:44.204 --> 15:47.294
[both hollering]

15:47.337 --> 15:49.296
[coins jangling]

15:49.339 --> 15:51.341
- You see that?

15:51.385 --> 15:54.127
Live long enough,
there's your reward.

15:54.170 --> 15:55.780
Breaking a hip tripping over
your oxygen tank

15:55.824 --> 15:57.652
just trying to get
to your bedpan.

15:57.695 --> 16:00.089
- Why don't more people
know about this?

16:00.133 --> 16:02.526
How come they never showed it
on "The Golden Girls"?

16:04.224 --> 16:07.314
- Lesbian fairytale.

16:07.357 --> 16:10.534
- They are talking to him
right now.

16:10.578 --> 16:13.407
- Of course, he wasn't
"Sonny" back then.

16:13.450 --> 16:16.149
Yeah, he was--he was still
"Louis Shineberg."

16:16.192 --> 16:19.195
He used to come to the show,
sit in the audience.

16:19.239 --> 16:22.633
He was a superfan,
if you know what I mean.

16:24.331 --> 16:27.029
I mean, it comes with
the territory in my business.

16:27.073 --> 16:28.596
Don't get me wrong,

16:28.639 --> 16:32.121
I love my little Douglets,
but after a certain point

16:32.165 --> 16:35.124
it gets, you know,
a little bit...

16:35.168 --> 16:37.605
- "Superfan-tastic"?

16:37.648 --> 16:39.563
- Creepy.
Skin-crawling.

16:39.607 --> 16:41.696
- Depressing?
- Somewhat.

16:41.739 --> 16:43.219
- Go on.

16:46.135 --> 16:48.703
Year after year,
he'd show up.

16:48.746 --> 16:50.748
Most kids grew out of it.

16:50.792 --> 16:53.447
Not him.

16:53.490 --> 16:56.189
We made friends.
Sort of.

16:56.232 --> 16:59.366
He said he wanted to be
an entertainer, like me.

16:59.409 --> 17:01.194
But it wasn't until...

17:01.237 --> 17:02.847
- Until what?

17:02.891 --> 17:05.502
- You're gonna think
I'm some kind of a nut job.

17:05.546 --> 17:08.201
- We're the ones who are crazy,
not you.

17:08.244 --> 17:10.899
Go ahead, dish.

17:10.942 --> 17:13.815
- Those things...

17:13.858 --> 17:16.383
The Wishees.

17:16.426 --> 17:19.603
I still remember the first time
he showed up with them.

17:19.647 --> 17:21.388
The costumes.

17:21.431 --> 17:24.217
The big round fish eyes.

17:24.260 --> 17:27.176
The "fuck me" mouths.

17:27.220 --> 17:30.571
Let's face it,
Louis was just a schmuck

17:30.614 --> 17:33.269
until those candy-colored
abominations came along.

17:33.313 --> 17:37.099
After that,
everything changed for him.

17:37.143 --> 17:39.797
Suddenly, he just took...

17:39.841 --> 17:41.756
whatever he wanted to.

17:41.799 --> 17:44.411
Starting with my show.

17:44.454 --> 17:46.630
- Oh, oh, question.

17:46.674 --> 17:49.198
Um, when these, uh,
whatever you call them--

17:49.242 --> 17:50.852
- "Wishees," Nick.
- Sax.

17:50.895 --> 17:53.115
- Which I am to understand
are basically, uh,

17:53.159 --> 17:55.161
shitheads in fuzzy outfits

17:55.204 --> 17:56.858
that dance around the stage
with Mr. Shineberg--

17:56.901 --> 18:00.949
when they, as you say,
"showed up"...

18:00.992 --> 18:03.778
are we saying, like--
say, for example,

18:03.821 --> 18:06.563
from Cleveland?

18:06.607 --> 18:08.870
- "Cleveland."
Cleveland, Ohio.

18:08.913 --> 18:10.393
- Yes.

18:10.437 --> 18:12.439
- By way of
the Crab Nebula, maybe.

18:12.482 --> 18:13.788
- Ah-ha.

18:13.831 --> 18:17.444
- And they weren't just
guys in outfits.

18:17.487 --> 18:19.446
The big guy doesn't seem
very bright,

18:19.489 --> 18:22.753
so I'm gonna try to make this
as simple as I can.

18:22.797 --> 18:24.407
Back in the Etruscan age,

18:24.451 --> 18:27.628
this gigantic meteor
crashes into Earth--

18:27.671 --> 18:29.586
- All right, that's it.
I'm done.

18:29.630 --> 18:31.893
Enjoy your interrogation.
- Where the fuck are you going?

18:31.936 --> 18:33.634
- I'm simply famished,
so I'm gonna find

18:33.677 --> 18:35.766
where they stashed those
pudding cups or die trying.

18:35.810 --> 18:37.594
You, Trigger.

18:37.638 --> 18:39.857
I suggest you come along.

18:39.901 --> 18:42.208
- Your friend is a little--
- I know.

18:44.297 --> 18:45.776
Keep talking.

18:45.820 --> 18:48.779
[sinister music]

18:48.823 --> 18:51.521
♪

18:51.565 --> 18:54.307
[children chattering]

18:54.350 --> 18:56.787
♪

18:56.831 --> 18:58.702
- [grunts]

18:58.746 --> 19:02.315
- [gasps] You.

19:02.358 --> 19:04.012
- You know what they say:

19:04.055 --> 19:07.494
"Nothing makes you believe
in Hell like Catholic school."

19:07.537 --> 19:09.235
- [gasps]
No, wait!

19:09.278 --> 19:11.498
- Wait, Hailey.

19:11.541 --> 19:13.195
I'm sorry.

19:13.239 --> 19:15.328
I am so, so sorry
for everything that happened.

19:15.371 --> 19:17.243
- Get away from me.
- Don't--don't run off, please.

19:17.286 --> 19:18.548
I'm not moving.
See?

19:18.592 --> 19:20.637
I'll stay perfectly still.

19:20.681 --> 19:22.639
I wouldn't think
of hurting you.

19:22.683 --> 19:24.032
It's--it's the opposite.

19:24.075 --> 19:26.861
I--I've been
protecting you, haven't I?

19:26.904 --> 19:28.689
I'm just a boy...

19:28.732 --> 19:30.734
standing in front of a girl

19:30.778 --> 19:33.215
asking her to listen.

19:33.259 --> 19:34.869
I don't blame you
for being scared.

19:34.912 --> 19:37.872
This can be very confusing.

19:37.915 --> 19:39.613
Should we sit?
[stammers]

19:39.656 --> 19:41.397
Would that be better?

19:43.747 --> 19:46.359
I see you've got
your lucky keychain.

19:46.402 --> 19:47.882
Maybe you've been
thinking about things.

19:47.925 --> 19:50.885
Questions you have for me.

19:50.928 --> 19:53.322
- You're supposed to be dead.

19:53.366 --> 19:55.019
- "Dead."

19:55.063 --> 19:57.718
Someone told you that?

19:57.761 --> 19:59.285
- My parents.

19:59.328 --> 20:01.374
- Ah, parents.

20:01.417 --> 20:02.853
[chuckles softly]
They do like

20:02.897 --> 20:05.639
making up stories,
don't they?

20:05.682 --> 20:07.380
Seems that...

20:07.423 --> 20:09.556
no one wants to tell you
the truth these days.

20:12.385 --> 20:14.735
- What happened to your eye?

20:14.778 --> 20:17.738
[ominous music]

20:17.781 --> 20:19.740
♪

20:19.783 --> 20:21.568
- You're not the only one
who knows what it's like

20:21.611 --> 20:22.873
to be bullied.

20:26.399 --> 20:30.490
What if I told you that
I was forced to do what I did?

20:30.533 --> 20:33.754
There are very awful people
in this world, Hailey,

20:33.797 --> 20:37.279
and they can make people
do very awful things.

20:37.323 --> 20:39.455
♪

20:39.499 --> 20:42.415
Doesn't make it right,
but it's the truth.

20:42.458 --> 20:43.590
♪

20:43.633 --> 20:45.374
I was happy

20:45.418 --> 20:48.682
when you children were saved
by the police.

20:48.725 --> 20:50.597
Those very awful people?

20:50.640 --> 20:51.815
Not so much.

20:53.382 --> 20:55.776
As you can see.

20:55.819 --> 20:57.952
♪

20:57.995 --> 21:00.520
I'm sorry, I--I can
put my glasses back on.

21:00.563 --> 21:03.479
- So now we're supposed
to be friends?

21:03.523 --> 21:04.959
I don't need friends.

21:06.917 --> 21:08.789
- I do.

21:08.832 --> 21:10.312
♪

21:10.356 --> 21:11.922
But...

21:11.966 --> 21:14.360
if that's the way you feel...

21:14.403 --> 21:17.537
I'm just happy that you're
finally hearing the truth.

21:17.580 --> 21:19.582
You've been lied to
since the day you were born.

21:19.626 --> 21:20.844
It's about time
someone finally--

21:20.888 --> 21:22.890
- What's that supposed to mean?

21:22.933 --> 21:24.631
[music darkens]

21:24.674 --> 21:25.980
No, no.

21:26.023 --> 21:29.766
I'm not one
to open up old wounds.

21:29.810 --> 21:32.813
But you do know
the whole story?

21:32.856 --> 21:36.077
Your father lied to your mother
and then ran out on her.

21:36.120 --> 21:38.732
And then your mother lied
to your father about you,

21:38.775 --> 21:40.777
and then to you
about your father.

21:40.821 --> 21:43.563
I'm not a shrink,
but that is a rough place

21:43.606 --> 21:44.999
for any kid to start.

21:45.042 --> 21:47.349
- I'm going.

21:49.220 --> 21:51.484
- Wait!

21:51.527 --> 21:52.615
♪

21:52.659 --> 21:53.964
One last thing.

21:54.008 --> 21:56.053
When you get home
and see your mother,

21:56.097 --> 21:57.664
tell her we met.

21:57.707 --> 21:58.839
Tell her what I said.

21:58.882 --> 22:00.667
Be honest with her.

22:00.710 --> 22:02.495
See what she says.

22:02.538 --> 22:03.626
And if you don't want
to be friends,

22:03.670 --> 22:05.019
you will never see me again.

22:05.062 --> 22:06.803
But if you do,

22:06.847 --> 22:10.546
just say the word
and I'll be right there.

22:10.590 --> 22:17.597
♪

22:21.862 --> 22:24.430
- While others run in fear

22:24.473 --> 22:27.389
from those who've declared war
on Easter,

22:27.433 --> 22:30.827
one man will unite us all...

22:30.871 --> 22:35.745
In bringing sexy back
to Easter.

22:35.789 --> 22:40.402
♪

22:40.446 --> 22:44.406
This year,
if we don't celebrate Easter,

22:44.450 --> 22:46.190
they win.

22:46.234 --> 22:50.456
♪

22:50.499 --> 22:52.501
[music continues
over speakers]

22:52.545 --> 22:54.198
- Just a taste.

22:54.242 --> 22:56.810
A little,
como se dice,flavor,

22:56.853 --> 22:59.595
if you will.

22:59.639 --> 23:01.380
This ain't
your grandma's Easter,

23:01.423 --> 23:02.555
am I right?

23:02.598 --> 23:04.644
♪

23:04.687 --> 23:05.819
Well?

23:05.862 --> 23:08.212
Kap?

23:08.256 --> 23:10.084
What do you think?

23:10.127 --> 23:12.129
♪

23:12.173 --> 23:14.218
- [hollering]
- Go, Kap, go!

23:14.262 --> 23:16.438
[laughing] Whoo-hoo!

23:16.482 --> 23:20.311
♪

23:20.355 --> 23:22.879
- I think it's
fucking brilliant.

23:22.923 --> 23:25.882
[applause]

23:25.926 --> 23:32.715
♪

23:32.759 --> 23:36.240
- Oh, there she is!
[laughing]

23:36.284 --> 23:38.373
Who's hungry?
[laughs]

23:38.417 --> 23:40.114
- If you'd told me one day

23:40.157 --> 23:42.464
I'd get to see Dayglo Doug
up close and in person,

23:42.508 --> 23:44.423
tell the story
of how he met Sonny Shine

23:44.466 --> 23:46.381
for the first time,
well, I would have said,

23:46.425 --> 23:48.165
"Holy guacamole,
somebody pinch me

23:48.209 --> 23:50.907
because this is
a dream come true!"

23:50.951 --> 23:52.779
But it's not.

23:52.822 --> 23:54.911
- Yeah, well,
if it's any consolation,

23:54.955 --> 23:57.218
that look on your face
of soul-crushing disappointment

23:57.261 --> 23:59.438
has been the highlight
of this whole trip.

24:01.744 --> 24:04.486
[man shouting in German]

24:04.530 --> 24:06.488
Sieg Heil!

24:06.532 --> 24:09.317
- Dickless freaking Doug.

24:09.360 --> 24:10.753
Some witness.

24:10.797 --> 24:12.668
That's what I get
for trusting Mer.

24:15.454 --> 24:17.151
- You should be the black one.

24:17.194 --> 24:19.240
- I was black last time!

24:19.283 --> 24:21.503
- I'm not a schwarzer!

24:21.547 --> 24:24.201
You be the schwarzer!

24:24.245 --> 24:25.638
- Is that gonna be us
someday, Nick?

24:25.681 --> 24:28.597
Frittering away our last days
in a place like this,

24:28.641 --> 24:30.469
arguing over some silly game?

24:30.512 --> 24:31.905
- Don't you worry
about that, pal.

24:31.948 --> 24:33.646
I'll drink bleach
before I let that happen.

24:33.689 --> 24:35.299
Besides, what are you
worried about?

24:35.343 --> 24:37.258
You haven't even hit
the magical "P-word" yet.

24:38.738 --> 24:40.479
"Puberty."

24:40.522 --> 24:42.698
It's Latin for "pubes."

24:42.742 --> 24:45.614
Six-year period where you part
your hair down the middle

24:45.658 --> 24:48.487
and your body gets
all awkward and, uh, pimply.

24:48.530 --> 24:50.663
At the same, it wants
to get naked with other people.

24:50.706 --> 24:52.926
- But what if I don't want
to grow up?

24:52.969 --> 24:54.580
- Well, then you're gonna have
to file that one

24:54.623 --> 24:57.321
under "tough shit."

24:57.365 --> 24:58.888
[man shouting in German]

24:58.932 --> 25:01.325
- Um...

25:01.369 --> 25:04.328
[sinister music]

25:04.372 --> 25:06.200
♪

25:06.243 --> 25:08.463
Have you noticed
the staff here is funny?

25:08.507 --> 25:10.639
I mean, usually the people
they hire in joints like this

25:10.683 --> 25:12.685
are, um...

25:12.728 --> 25:14.513
different.

25:14.556 --> 25:16.950
- "Different" how?
- Dominican.

25:16.993 --> 25:19.256
- [sniffing]

25:19.300 --> 25:20.910
Do you smell popcorn?

25:20.954 --> 25:23.391
- Oh, hell yeah.

25:23.434 --> 25:26.394
[muffled peppy
militaristic music]

25:26.437 --> 25:33.444
♪

25:36.709 --> 25:38.885
Holy shiesse.

25:38.928 --> 25:40.713
♪

25:42.802 --> 25:44.760
Hey, Mer.

25:44.804 --> 25:47.371
Mer.
Guess what?

25:47.415 --> 25:48.895
Turns out this place
is a home for assholes.

25:48.938 --> 25:50.461
- Excuse me?

25:50.505 --> 25:51.898
- Go ahead, tell her.
- [stammering]

25:51.941 --> 25:53.421
Some of the people here
are a bit colorful.

25:53.464 --> 25:54.727
- Yeah, red, white, and black.

25:54.770 --> 25:56.816
We saw the tape,
der fuckward.

25:56.859 --> 25:59.340
- Look, you know Sonny's M.O.
I was set up.

25:59.383 --> 26:00.559
- If the armband fits.

26:00.602 --> 26:02.517
- I am a history buff.

26:02.561 --> 26:05.520
A collector of rare
and exotic memorabilia.

26:05.564 --> 26:08.001
I don't belong here
with these fascists.

26:08.044 --> 26:09.872
- Okay, can someone
please explain to me

26:09.916 --> 26:10.873
what the hell is going on?

26:10.917 --> 26:12.396
- Nazis, Mer.

26:12.440 --> 26:13.876
The place is stinking
with them.

26:13.920 --> 26:16.705
- It wasn't enough
that he stole my show.

26:16.749 --> 26:19.403
Then he has to twist the knife.

26:19.447 --> 26:21.362
You know, Sonny used to say

26:21.405 --> 26:22.493
that the shortest book
ever written

26:22.537 --> 26:24.321
was the German book of humor?

26:24.365 --> 26:26.846
That's why he stuck me here!

26:26.889 --> 26:29.805
Don't you think I'd leave
if I could?

26:29.849 --> 26:32.721
I've been bombing
in front of this Stasiscum

26:32.765 --> 26:34.418
for a decade.

26:34.462 --> 26:37.508
I mean, you gotta get me out
of this place!

26:37.552 --> 26:40.294
♪ I can't take
another bad review ♪

26:40.337 --> 26:41.643
- We're going, come on.
- No, no, no.

26:41.687 --> 26:43.297
We're not actually
taking this guy.

26:43.340 --> 26:44.733
- You said you would
protect me if I talked.

26:44.777 --> 26:46.430
- This adult-diaper-wearing
war criminal

26:46.474 --> 26:47.649
is not getting in my cab.

26:47.693 --> 26:50.696
- Hey, I resemble
that last remark.

26:50.739 --> 26:52.306
- Hey.

26:52.349 --> 26:53.873
- I'm not doing this
with you right now.

26:53.916 --> 26:56.005
- What is it about this guy?
- [clears throat]

26:56.049 --> 26:57.790
[claps, whistles]

26:57.833 --> 27:01.402
Visiting time, sadly, is over.

27:01.445 --> 27:04.318
So we're gonna have
to ask you to leave.

27:04.361 --> 27:05.885
[foreboding music]

27:05.928 --> 27:07.974
It's time for your pills.

27:08.017 --> 27:10.019
- We have some more questions
to ask him off-site.

27:10.063 --> 27:11.934
I'm sure you understand.

27:11.978 --> 27:13.588
- I don't think so.

27:13.632 --> 27:14.589
- [sighs]

27:14.633 --> 27:17.070
♪

27:17.113 --> 27:19.420
You eye-fucking me, Nietzsche?

27:20.813 --> 27:22.945
- Uh, Nick?

27:22.989 --> 27:28.647
♪

27:28.690 --> 27:30.649
- Is there a problem,
young man?

27:30.692 --> 27:32.781
- Nothing we can't handle,
Herr Zimmer.

27:32.825 --> 27:34.696
- Oh, boy.
- You!

27:34.740 --> 27:36.655
Where do you think
you're slinking off to?

27:36.698 --> 27:39.483
You have a show
in 20 minutes.

27:39.527 --> 27:40.833
[sinister music]

27:40.876 --> 27:43.836
[man shouting in German]

27:43.879 --> 27:45.620
♪

27:45.664 --> 27:48.492
[whistle blowing]

27:48.536 --> 27:50.756
♪

27:50.799 --> 27:52.758
[chanting]
Sieg Heil!

27:52.801 --> 27:55.108
Sieg Heil!

27:55.151 --> 27:57.632
Sieg Heil!

27:57.676 --> 27:59.678
Sieg Heil!

27:59.721 --> 28:01.027
Sieg Heil!

28:04.552 --> 28:07.598
- Well, actually,
the show starts now.

28:07.642 --> 28:09.818
- Blitzkrieg!

28:09.862 --> 28:12.516
[funky music]

28:12.560 --> 28:14.518
[electronic scream]

28:14.562 --> 28:16.825
- All right, NYPD!
Nobody move!

28:16.869 --> 28:18.914
Shit.
- [hollers]

28:18.958 --> 28:20.568
[gunshot]

28:20.611 --> 28:22.048
- Fuck!

28:22.091 --> 28:25.181
Doug!
- [hollers]

28:25.225 --> 28:27.401
- [sniffs]

28:27.444 --> 28:30.099
[grunting]

28:30.143 --> 28:32.536
- [gagging]
- [yelps]

28:32.580 --> 28:33.929
- [laughs]

28:33.973 --> 28:36.192
[grunting]

28:36.236 --> 28:37.846
- Nick!

28:37.890 --> 28:40.675
♪

28:40.719 --> 28:42.851
- [screams]

28:42.895 --> 28:44.853
♪

28:44.897 --> 28:46.768
- That's my witness.

28:46.812 --> 28:48.552
- [screaming]

28:48.596 --> 28:49.902
- Lookit, Mer!

28:49.945 --> 28:52.600
His bones are so brittle!

28:52.643 --> 28:59.563
♪

29:02.958 --> 29:04.743
- Ah!

29:04.786 --> 29:07.571
- [grunting]

29:07.615 --> 29:08.747
[growling]

29:08.790 --> 29:10.487
- Sax, stop killing people!

29:10.531 --> 29:12.881
- Ah, come on, Mer!
They're Nazis!

29:12.925 --> 29:15.014
[laughs]

29:15.057 --> 29:22.021
♪

29:22.064 --> 29:23.805
- Ouch-witz!

29:23.849 --> 29:30.638
♪

29:30.681 --> 29:33.641
- [gagging]

29:33.684 --> 29:40.648
♪

29:40.691 --> 29:42.824
- [sniffs]

29:42.868 --> 29:46.785
♪

29:46.828 --> 29:48.264
- [hollers]

29:48.308 --> 29:51.267
- [gagging]

29:51.311 --> 29:53.661
♪

29:53.704 --> 29:56.533
Papa never loved me.

29:56.577 --> 29:58.492
[groans]

29:58.535 --> 30:01.669
♪

30:01.712 --> 30:04.063
Auf weidersehen,
motherfucker.

30:07.022 --> 30:10.069
"Greatest generation" my ass.

30:16.379 --> 30:18.991
[gate clattering]

30:24.344 --> 30:25.693
- Oh, my God.

30:25.736 --> 30:27.477
Look at what they did to you.

30:27.521 --> 30:30.089
- Get off of me!
Get off of me!

30:30.132 --> 30:31.830
[stammering]
Fuck!

30:31.873 --> 30:33.744
Get off of me!

30:38.706 --> 30:40.708
- Is it true?

30:40.751 --> 30:42.753
- What?

30:42.797 --> 30:45.191
- You killed all them Russians
in the toilet.

30:47.062 --> 30:49.630
- What if it is?
- [scoffs]

30:52.807 --> 30:55.418
[sighs]

30:55.462 --> 30:57.507
It's like...

30:57.551 --> 31:00.336
It's like you're
two different people.

31:00.380 --> 31:03.035
One's warm and loving.

31:03.078 --> 31:04.732
The other's just...

31:04.775 --> 31:06.168
cold and cruel.

31:06.212 --> 31:08.301
- No! No!

31:08.344 --> 31:10.172
Don't say that!

31:10.216 --> 31:12.174
I'm not two different people!

31:12.218 --> 31:14.698
It's just me, and I am--

31:14.742 --> 31:16.222
I'm Blue!

31:17.701 --> 31:20.182
I'm Blue!

31:20.226 --> 31:22.793
- Orcus.

31:22.837 --> 31:25.579
- This is...

31:25.622 --> 31:27.755
[grunts]
Ow.

31:30.758 --> 31:32.542
I'm sorry.

31:35.632 --> 31:37.547
I'm sorry.

31:37.591 --> 31:39.636
[sighs]

31:39.680 --> 31:43.249
You've been so kind to me,
and, um...

31:45.294 --> 31:47.557
I've spurned you.

31:47.601 --> 31:49.124
- You haven't, though.

31:49.168 --> 31:51.822
I mean, "spurned."

31:51.866 --> 31:53.650
- No, I spurned you.

31:53.694 --> 31:55.130
- You really haven't.

31:56.653 --> 31:59.700
- I've treated you unkindly,
and...

31:59.743 --> 32:02.746
[sighs]
I'm just...

32:02.790 --> 32:04.487
I'm scared, Pink.

32:05.749 --> 32:08.752
I need you tell me that...

32:08.796 --> 32:10.754
[sighs]

32:10.798 --> 32:13.235
That it's me, right?

32:13.279 --> 32:15.455
I'm Blue Scaramucci.

32:15.498 --> 32:19.154
T-tell me I'm Blue Scaramucci.

32:19.198 --> 32:20.851
- Yeah.

32:20.895 --> 32:23.506
It's you.

32:23.550 --> 32:25.639
That's right.

32:25.682 --> 32:27.641
You're Blue.

32:27.684 --> 32:30.513
You're Blue Scaramucci.

32:30.557 --> 32:33.516
[eerie music]

32:33.560 --> 32:35.344
♪

32:35.388 --> 32:37.259
- [growling]

32:37.303 --> 32:38.391
- [whimpers]

32:38.434 --> 32:41.263
- Oh, you nasty little tart.

32:41.307 --> 32:42.786
Go on.

32:42.830 --> 32:46.181
Oh, tell me, tell me.

32:46.225 --> 32:47.617
- [hollers]

32:47.661 --> 32:49.793
- Who am I?

32:49.837 --> 32:51.795
- [whimpers]

32:51.839 --> 32:55.277
- ♪ Ooh, Sunny

32:55.321 --> 32:56.670
[peppy music]

32:56.713 --> 32:59.760
♪ Ooh, Sunny Shine

32:59.803 --> 33:01.283
♪ Ooh

33:01.327 --> 33:02.763
- [laughing]

33:02.806 --> 33:06.941
Sock it to me!
[whooping]

33:06.985 --> 33:08.987
♪

33:09.030 --> 33:12.381
- Dad, look here!

33:12.425 --> 33:15.602
- Dad, look!

33:15.645 --> 33:18.561
It's Sonny Shine's
original shiny mic!

33:18.605 --> 33:21.216
- I don't know
how "original" it is.

33:21.260 --> 33:22.957
- It says on the thing!

33:23.001 --> 33:24.872
- I mean, when I was growing up

33:24.915 --> 33:27.353
it was the
"Dayglo Doug Power Hour."

33:27.396 --> 33:30.660
All this stuff
is from that show.

33:30.704 --> 33:33.620
I'm sure you can still find
the old clips online.

33:33.663 --> 33:35.404
- Who likes selfies?

33:35.448 --> 33:36.971
- Oh, my God!
[both hollering]

33:37.015 --> 33:38.755
- Let's do this!
Let's do this.

33:38.799 --> 33:40.583
Come on.
Gather around, everyone.

33:40.627 --> 33:42.846
Give that to me.
Okay, here we are.

33:42.890 --> 33:44.674
Everybody say,

33:44.718 --> 33:47.547
"Sonny Shine Easter
Live Bonanza Extravaganza

33:47.590 --> 33:49.810
With Tony Danza!"

33:49.853 --> 33:51.507
[all cheering]

33:51.551 --> 33:53.422
All right, all right,
y'all better get going.

33:53.466 --> 33:56.860
The Wishee exhibit closes
in 20 minutes for fumigation.

33:56.904 --> 33:58.427
Remember, when you post those:

33:58.471 --> 34:01.865
#SonnyEaster.

34:01.909 --> 34:04.868
- Make Easter great again!

34:04.912 --> 34:07.610
- And a MEGA day to you, too.

34:07.654 --> 34:10.613
[eerie music]

34:10.657 --> 34:14.574
♪

34:14.617 --> 34:18.317
[birds chirping]

34:18.360 --> 34:22.364
- So the procedure is for
a root canal on Saturday.

34:22.408 --> 34:25.367
And the payment's been made?

34:25.411 --> 34:26.934
Hailey?
- Hi, Dr. Reddy.

34:26.977 --> 34:28.762
I need to tell
my mother something.

34:28.805 --> 34:30.981
It's important.

34:31.025 --> 34:33.767
- Hailey, your mother
doesn't work here anymore.

34:33.810 --> 34:35.551
- But...

34:35.595 --> 34:37.423
since when?

34:37.466 --> 34:39.425
- A few days ago.

34:39.468 --> 34:41.905
Sorry, I thought
she would have told you.

34:41.949 --> 34:43.733
[dark calliope music]

34:43.777 --> 34:45.996
Lollipop?

34:46.040 --> 34:50.436
♪

34:53.656 --> 34:55.571
- It's...

34:55.615 --> 34:56.920
fantastic.

34:56.964 --> 34:58.922
- I knew you'd love it.
- [exclaims]

34:58.966 --> 35:02.056
It's like a 3D version
of the inside of my brain.

35:02.100 --> 35:03.449
- I know, right?

35:03.492 --> 35:05.451
- You really are on the level.

35:05.494 --> 35:07.888
- You said they weren't
guys in suits.

35:07.931 --> 35:10.586
I--I'm afraid to ask, but...

35:10.630 --> 35:12.806
what exactly
did you mean by that?

35:12.849 --> 35:16.636
- Afraid to ask,
or afraid of the answer?

35:16.679 --> 35:18.768
- You ever talk to one of them
face to face?

35:18.812 --> 35:20.596
- Oh, uh, no.

35:20.640 --> 35:22.424
See, about that--
they don't speak.

35:22.468 --> 35:23.904
- What do you mean?
- [scoffs]

35:23.947 --> 35:26.515
I mean, they don't speak.

35:26.559 --> 35:28.822
- Like Helen Keller
or like a mime?

35:28.865 --> 35:30.432
- No, no, no.

35:30.476 --> 35:32.739
No, they communicate
through telepathy.

35:32.782 --> 35:35.437
- Of course.
- Uh, only Sonny can hear them.

35:35.481 --> 35:39.354
They speak, it goes
straight into his brain.

35:39.398 --> 35:40.921
Don't think it would
work so well for you, but--

35:40.964 --> 35:43.358
- [huffs]
I'm gonna be in the kitchen.

35:43.402 --> 35:45.839
If you got tinfoil,
I can make Doug a new hat.

35:48.581 --> 35:50.409
- Who'd believe a guy
with a smile like that

35:50.452 --> 35:52.324
could be so evil?

35:53.629 --> 35:54.978
- [sighs]

35:55.022 --> 35:56.806
What, that Mr. Pussy Pants
is a bad guy?

35:56.850 --> 35:59.505
Welcome to the party.
- I couldn't believe it.

35:59.548 --> 36:02.638
Me and Hailey used to...
[sighs]

36:02.682 --> 36:04.684
But I guess that's
all over now.

36:04.727 --> 36:06.076
It's like you said, Nick.

36:06.120 --> 36:08.731
People change.
Everything changes.

36:08.775 --> 36:11.908
- Uh, that's right.
That goes for me, too.

36:11.952 --> 36:14.084
Try and knock me off the...
[stammering]

36:14.128 --> 36:16.478
Try and knock me off the wagon.

36:16.522 --> 36:17.827
Will of iron, pal.

36:17.871 --> 36:19.655
She ain't gonna be happy

36:19.699 --> 36:22.005
until I've broken every promise
to Amanda and the kid.

36:22.049 --> 36:24.443
And for what, huh?

36:24.486 --> 36:26.009
On a wild goose chase

36:26.053 --> 36:28.882
with some incontinent
Kraut-dog

36:28.925 --> 36:31.711
who thinks Sasquatch
killed Biggie.

36:31.754 --> 36:33.452
- What are we gonna do, Nick?

36:35.193 --> 36:36.977
- Well, for now, I'm gonna
get this jelly open.

36:37.020 --> 36:39.458
- I mean about Sunny and--
and the Wishees.

36:39.501 --> 36:41.808
Doug says...

36:41.851 --> 36:43.679
- Let me tell you something.

36:43.723 --> 36:46.073
Being a grown-up
means you've gotta learn

36:46.116 --> 36:49.468
that heroism comes
in a lot of different forms,

36:49.511 --> 36:52.732
one of them being
not being a hero.

36:52.775 --> 36:54.516
Capische?
[grunts]

36:54.560 --> 36:56.605
- Nick, you don't really
believe that.

37:00.783 --> 37:02.611
- This is what I believe in.

37:02.655 --> 37:04.744
Being there for that kid.

37:04.787 --> 37:06.833
Trying to give her
some kind of normal life

37:06.876 --> 37:09.401
after everything
she has been through.

37:09.444 --> 37:11.794
And, you know, we got
too many freaks in leotards

37:11.838 --> 37:15.058
in our lives for my taste.

37:15.102 --> 37:17.583
Fuck them all.

37:17.626 --> 37:19.628
- I killed it.

37:19.672 --> 37:21.456
[Wishee screeching]

37:21.500 --> 37:22.805
- I know I did.

37:22.849 --> 37:24.633
Nothing bleeds that much
and walks away.

37:24.677 --> 37:26.896
But when I went back,
it was gone.

37:26.940 --> 37:28.768
Something moved the body.

37:28.811 --> 37:31.074
I had a feeling
the place would be wiped clean

37:31.118 --> 37:32.598
before forensics got there.

37:32.641 --> 37:34.730
What they don't know

37:34.774 --> 37:37.255
is I took some
of whatever it was

37:37.298 --> 37:38.995
that came out of that thing.

37:39.039 --> 37:41.476
- You have its blood?
Where is it?

37:41.520 --> 37:44.914
- Well, I had it in here
under a lamp.

37:44.958 --> 37:47.613
Then it started moving,
like it was trying to get out.

37:47.656 --> 37:48.831
- No, no, no.

37:48.875 --> 37:49.963
You're supposed
to keep it cold.

37:50.006 --> 37:51.704
- I figured that.

37:51.747 --> 37:54.446
I put it in a jelly jar,
I stuck it in the fridge.

37:54.489 --> 37:57.144
[sinister music]

37:59.538 --> 38:01.714
- Oh, man, I needed that.

38:01.757 --> 38:03.716
I tell you I got
a blood sugar thing?

38:03.759 --> 38:06.588
[stomach gurgling]

38:12.333 --> 38:14.770
[groaning]

38:14.814 --> 38:18.165
♪

38:18.208 --> 38:20.646
[grunts]

38:20.689 --> 38:22.169
♪

38:22.212 --> 38:23.779
[goofy grunting]

38:23.823 --> 38:26.565
[gasps, groans]

38:26.608 --> 38:28.654
Sweet boneless Jesus.

38:28.697 --> 38:31.178
[farting, liquid gurgling]

38:31.221 --> 38:34.224
[gags, groans]

38:34.268 --> 38:36.009
This is Captain Turdwell.

38:36.052 --> 38:38.794
We are experiencing
uncontrollable explosive thrust

38:38.838 --> 38:40.187
in both engines!

38:40.230 --> 38:42.320
Prepare for water landing!

38:42.363 --> 38:44.670
- How about a courtesy flush?

38:44.713 --> 38:48.021
[farting, liquid gurgling]

38:48.064 --> 38:49.805
- Whoo!

38:49.849 --> 38:51.285
[laughs]

38:51.329 --> 38:54.157
[inhuman screeching]

38:54.201 --> 39:00.207
♪

39:00.250 --> 39:02.209
Ow!

39:02.252 --> 39:04.559
♪

39:04.603 --> 39:06.256
[babbles]

39:06.300 --> 39:13.307
♪

39:16.832 --> 39:19.182
- Sax!

39:19.226 --> 39:20.662
[dramatic music]

39:20.706 --> 39:22.360
- [hollering]

39:22.403 --> 39:25.232
Go back to hell!
[hollering indistinctly]

39:25.275 --> 39:28.366
[creature shrieking]

39:28.409 --> 39:30.759
- [hollers]

39:30.803 --> 39:33.719
[panting]

39:38.158 --> 39:41.248
[ominous rumbling, gurgling]

39:41.291 --> 39:43.903
[yelps]

39:43.946 --> 39:47.820
♪

39:47.863 --> 39:49.952
[hollering]

39:49.996 --> 39:52.041
[groans]

39:52.085 --> 39:55.088
[both shrieking]

40:06.708 --> 40:10.669
- You must be
Rin Tin Tikki Tavi

40:10.712 --> 40:13.062
walking in here.

40:13.106 --> 40:14.324
- If I can forgive you

40:14.368 --> 40:16.979
sending six of your chums in
to kill me,

40:17.023 --> 40:19.025
then surely...

40:19.068 --> 40:20.461
surely...

40:20.505 --> 40:23.072
you can forgive me
for merely...

40:23.116 --> 40:25.771
drowning them all
in the toilet.

40:25.814 --> 40:28.774
Besides, I'm here
to make you an offer

40:28.817 --> 40:32.647
that you simply cannot refuse.

40:34.170 --> 40:37.478
There are those that would give
their right hand

40:37.522 --> 40:39.132
to work with me.

40:39.175 --> 40:42.483
- Just because you talk
like Liam Neeson...

40:42.527 --> 40:44.006
[clicks tongue]

40:44.050 --> 40:46.531
This does not make you
Liam Neeson.

40:46.574 --> 40:48.707
- [chuckles]

40:48.750 --> 40:50.709
In ages past, it was customary

40:50.752 --> 40:53.538
to sacrifice black sheep
in my name.

40:53.581 --> 40:55.496
And then...

40:55.540 --> 40:58.151
should make a lovely,
big pot of stew.

40:58.194 --> 41:00.327
Not unlike this one.

41:00.370 --> 41:03.330
[mellow wind music]

41:03.373 --> 41:07.203
♪

41:07.247 --> 41:10.250
[speaking Russian]

41:24.743 --> 41:26.527
Maybe you young pioneers

41:26.571 --> 41:28.355
are more familiar
with the Bible

41:28.398 --> 41:30.662
than you are
with the Roman texts.

41:30.705 --> 41:32.490
♪

41:32.533 --> 41:34.143
Yeah?

41:34.187 --> 41:37.364
For example...

41:37.407 --> 41:40.236
"He who fails to find me

41:40.280 --> 41:42.630
injures himself."

41:42.674 --> 41:44.240
[music darkens]

41:44.284 --> 41:47.200
- The fuck?

41:47.243 --> 41:50.595
- "And if your hand
should cause you to sin..."

41:50.638 --> 41:52.553
♪

41:52.597 --> 41:54.642
"Cut it off.

41:54.686 --> 41:57.427
Throw it away."

41:57.471 --> 42:00.430
- [hollering]

42:00.474 --> 42:02.476
♪

42:02.520 --> 42:04.522
- And what is that other verse?

42:04.565 --> 42:06.262
Oh, yes.
[babbles]

42:06.306 --> 42:08.308
"Beware of the dogs,

42:08.351 --> 42:10.702
"beware of
the evil workers..."

42:10.745 --> 42:13.139
[dishes clattering]

42:13.182 --> 42:14.575
- "And beware

42:14.619 --> 42:17.186
of false circumcision."

42:17.230 --> 42:19.841
- [groaning, whimpering]

42:19.885 --> 42:22.322
[screaming]

42:23.584 --> 42:26.544
- [speaking Russian]

42:26.587 --> 42:28.110
[knives clatter]

42:29.851 --> 42:33.159
- Now, here's the Bible
almost repeating itself,

42:33.202 --> 42:36.379
but not quite,
and the difference is crucial.

42:36.423 --> 42:38.860
"If your eye...

42:38.904 --> 42:41.471
causes you to sin..."

42:41.515 --> 42:43.604
- Eat shit, demon!

42:43.648 --> 42:45.214
- "Tear it out.

42:45.258 --> 42:46.607
Throw it away."

42:46.651 --> 42:48.914
- [screaming]

42:48.957 --> 42:51.743
♪

42:51.786 --> 42:55.616
- I am so taken by you guys.

42:55.660 --> 42:57.444
I really, really am.

42:57.487 --> 42:58.750
I walked in here

42:58.793 --> 42:59.925
and immediately
I'm saying to myself,

42:59.968 --> 43:01.535
"Oh, yes, yes.

43:01.579 --> 43:04.451
Here are some
proper nasty boys."

43:04.494 --> 43:07.759
My name is Orcus.

43:07.802 --> 43:10.239
♪

43:10.283 --> 43:12.502
Orcus.

43:16.811 --> 43:18.421
- Anything?

43:18.465 --> 43:20.641
- Uh, as far
as the residents go,

43:20.685 --> 43:23.905
they're practically dead
to begin with.

43:23.949 --> 43:25.646
- Well...
[sighs]

43:25.690 --> 43:28.170
We're nowhere on who took
the tape collection.

43:31.696 --> 43:35.177
But I think I might
have a bead...

43:35.221 --> 43:37.702
on who took Dayglo Doug.

43:37.745 --> 43:40.661
- A terrorist?

43:40.705 --> 43:42.794
- Shine's gonna want
to see this.

43:42.837 --> 43:46.536
[foreboding music]

43:46.580 --> 43:48.974
[keypad beeping]

43:49.017 --> 43:51.629
[device whirring]

43:51.672 --> 43:53.500
[door beeps]

43:53.543 --> 43:56.329
♪

43:56.372 --> 43:59.201
[inhuman screeching]

43:59.245 --> 44:06.252
♪

44:12.606 --> 44:15.565
[eerie gurgling]

44:15.609 --> 44:22.616
♪

44:33.583 --> 44:35.368
- Mm.

44:41.287 --> 44:42.418
- Mom?

44:42.462 --> 44:43.593
- Oh.

44:43.637 --> 44:45.508
Hi, sweetheart.

44:45.552 --> 44:48.468
- You're home a little late.

44:48.511 --> 44:51.427
- Yeah, work was kind of
a madhouse.

44:53.952 --> 44:56.258
It's the busiest time
of the year down at the clinic.

44:56.302 --> 44:57.390
Few months after Valentine's.

44:57.433 --> 45:00.480
Now, how was your day?

45:00.523 --> 45:01.699
How was school?

45:06.355 --> 45:08.575
Make any new friends?

45:08.618 --> 45:11.404
[ominous music]

